body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, this is Bryan Miller from Auto Solutions. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my name is Maria Brooks.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Maria! Can you please provide me with the first three digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Maria. Can you also confirm the last two digits of your address?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Maria. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Not really, I'm just feeling disappointed about the inventory at the dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand, Maria. We will work on improving our inventory selection. Thank you for bringing it to our attention.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Maria. Have a wonderful day! Goodbye.
